{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_019G9krarGLAsU6tdC8bYkpk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Here is the full implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation: Content-Hash-Triggered Rolling Restart for IstioCSR\n\n### Overview of changes\n\nThe implementation mirrors the trustmanager pattern in `pkg/controller/trustmanager/configmaps.go`:\n\n1. **New file** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go` — `readTrustedCABundle()`, `computeCABundleHash()`, `updateCABundleHashAnnotation()`\n2. **Modified** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go` — add `caBundleHashAnnotation` constant\n3. **Modified** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` — propagate CA bundle hash through the volume/ConfigMap creation chain and stamp it on the pod template\n4. **Modified** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go` — add template annotation comparison to `deploymentSpecModified`\n5. **New file** `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go` — unit tests for hash computation and annotation stamping\n\n---\n\n### File 1: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go` (NEW)\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\tappsv1 \"k8s.io/api/apps/v1\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\n// readTrustedCABundle reads the CNO-injected CA bundle from the operator namespace.\n// Returns the PEM bundle and any error.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) readTrustedCABundle() (string, error) {\n\tcm := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tkey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, key, cm); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(\n\t\t\terr,\n\t\t\t\"failed to read CA bundle ConfigMap %q in namespace %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundle, ok := cm.Data[common.TrustedCABundleKey]\n\tif !ok || caBundle == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"CA bundle ConfigMap %q does not contain key %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.TrustedCABundleKey)\n\t}\n\n\treturn caBundle, nil\n}\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hash of the CA bundle PEM content.\n// The hash is used as the pod template annotation to trigger rolling restarts\n// only when the actual certificate content changes.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n\n// updateCABundleHashAnnotation stamps the CA bundle content hash on the\n// deployment's pod template annotation. Changing this annotation triggers a\n// rolling restart when the CA bundle PEM content changes.\nfunc updateCABundleHashAnnotation(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, hash string) {\n\tif deployment.Spec.Template.Annotations == nil {\n\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t}\n\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations[caBundleHashAnnotation] = hash\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 2: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go` — ADD constant\n\nAdd this constant inside the first `const` block (after `caVolumeMountPath`):\n\n```go\n// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n// The hash covers PEM content (not resourceVersion) to trigger rolling restarts\n// only when the actual certificate data changes.\ncaBundleHashAnnotation = \"cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n```\n\nExact diff — in `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`, after line 27:\n\n```diff\n const (\n \tcaVolumeMountPath = \"/var/run/configmaps/istio-csr\"\n+\n+\t// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n+\tcaBundleHashAnnotation = \"cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n )\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 3: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` — Propagate hash\n\nThe changes are:\n\n**a)** `createOrUpdateCAConfigMap` returns `(string, error)` instead of `error`, returning the hash of `certData`:\n\n```go\n// createOrUpdateCAConfigMap creates or updates the CA ConfigMap with the provided certificate data.\n// Returns the SHA-256 hash of the certificate data and any error.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createOrUpdateCAConfigMap(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, certData string, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tif certData == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to find CA certificate\")\n\t}\n\n\tbundleHash := computeCABundleHash(certData)\n\n\tconfigmapKey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tName:      IstiocsrCAConfigMapName,\n\t\tNamespace: istiocsr.GetNamespace(),\n\t}\n\tfetched := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\texist, err := r.Exists(r.ctx, configmapKey, fetched)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check if CA configmap exists: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tdesired := &corev1.ConfigMap{\n\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\tName:      configmapKey.Name,\n\t\t\tNamespace: configmapKey.Namespace,\n\t\t\tLabels:    resourceLabels,\n\t\t},\n\t\tData: map[string]string{\n\t\t\tIstiocsrCAKeyName: certData,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tif exist && hasObjectChanged(desired, fetched) {\n\t\tr.log.V(1).Info(\"ca configmap need update\", \"name\", configmapKey)\n\t\tif err := r.UpdateWithRetry(r.ctx, desired); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update %s configmap resource: %w\", configmapKey, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tr.eventRecorder.Eventf(istiocsr, corev1.EventTypeNormal, \"Reconciled\", \"configmap resource %s reconciled back to desired state\", configmapKey)\n\t} else {\n\t\tr.log.V(4).Info(\"configmap resource already exists and is in expected state\", \"name\", configmapKey)\n\t}\n\n\tif !exist {\n\t\tif err := r.Create(r.ctx, desired); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create %s configmap resource: %w\", configmapKey, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tr.eventRecorder.Eventf(istiocsr, corev1.EventTypeNormal, \"Reconciled\", \"configmap resource %s created\", configmapKey)\n\t}\n\n\treturn bundleHash, nil\n}\n```\n\n**b)** `createCAConfigMapFromIssuerSecret` returns `(string, error)`:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createCAConfigMapFromIssuerSecret(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, issuerConfig certmanagerv1.IssuerConfig, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tif issuerConfig.CA.SecretName == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to fetch CA certificate configured for the %s issuer of CA type\", istiocsr.Spec.IstioCSRConfig.CertManager.IssuerRef.Name)\n\t}\n\n\tsecretKey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tName:      issuerConfig.CA.SecretName,\n\t\tNamespace: istiocsr.Spec.IstioCSRConfig.Istio.Namespace,\n\t}\n\tsecret := &corev1.Secret{}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, secretKey, secret); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to fetch secret in issuer: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := r.updateWatchLabel(secret, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\n\tcertData := string(secret.Data[IstiocsrCAKeyName])\n\treturn r.createOrUpdateCAConfigMap(istiocsr, certData, resourceLabels)\n}\n```\n\n**c)** `createCAConfigMapFromIstiodCertificate` returns `(string, error)`:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createCAConfigMapFromIstiodCertificate(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tistiodCertificate, err := r.getCertificateObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to fetch istiod certificate\")\n\t}\n\n\tsecretKey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tName:      istiodCertificate.Spec.SecretName,\n\t\tNamespace: istiodCertificate.GetNamespace(),\n\t}\n\tsecret := &corev1.Secret{}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, secretKey, secret); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to fetch secret in issuer: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := r.updateWatchLabel(secret, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\n\tcertData := string(secret.Data[IstiocsrCAKeyName])\n\treturn r.createOrUpdateCAConfigMap(istiocsr, certData, resourceLabels)\n}\n```\n\n**d)** `handleIssuerBasedCA` returns `(string, error)` and propagates the hash:\n\n```go\n// handleIssuerBasedCA handles the creation of CA ConfigMap from issuer secret and volume mounting.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) handleIssuerBasedCA(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tvar (\n\t\tissuerConfig certmanagerv1.IssuerConfig\n\t)\n\n\tobj, err := r.getIssuer(istiocsr)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to fetch issuer\")\n\t}\n\n\tissuerRefKind := strings.ToLower(istiocsr.Spec.IstioCSRConfig.CertManager.IssuerRef.Kind)\n\tswitch issuerRefKind {\n\tcase clusterIssuerKind:\n\t\tclusterIssuer, ok := obj.(*certmanagerv1.ClusterIssuer)\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(fmt.Errorf(\"failed to convert to ClusterIssuer\"), \"failed to fetch issuer\")\n\t\t}\n\t\tissuerConfig = clusterIssuer.Spec.IssuerConfig\n\tcase issuerKind:\n\t\tissuer, ok := obj.(*certmanagerv1.Issuer)\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(fmt.Errorf(\"failed to convert to Issuer\"), \"failed to fetch issuer\")\n\t\t}\n\t\tissuerConfig = issuer.Spec.IssuerConfig\n\t}\n\n\tshouldUpdateVolume := false\n\tvar bundleHash string\n\n\tif issuerConfig.CA != nil && issuerConfig.CA.SecretName != \"\" {\n\t\thash, err := r.createCAConfigMapFromIssuerSecret(istiocsr, issuerConfig, resourceLabels)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to create CA ConfigMap\")\n\t\t}\n\t\tbundleHash = hash\n\t\tshouldUpdateVolume = true\n\t}\n\n\tif issuerConfig.CA == nil {\n\t\thash, err := r.createCAConfigMapFromIstiodCertificate(istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to create CA ConfigMap\")\n\t\t}\n\t\tbundleHash = hash\n\t\tshouldUpdateVolume = true\n\t}\n\n\tif shouldUpdateVolume {\n\t\tupdateVolumeWithIssuerCA(deployment)\n\t}\n\n\treturn bundleHash, nil\n}\n```\n\n**e)** `handleUserProvidedCA` returns `(string, error)` and propagates the hash:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) handleUserProvidedCA(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tcaCertConfig := istiocsr.Spec.IstioCSRConfig.CertManager.IstioCACertificate\n\n\tnamespace := caCertConfig.Namespace\n\tif namespace == \"\" {\n\t\tnamespace = istiocsr.GetNamespace()\n\t}\n\n\tsourceConfigMapKey := types.NamespacedName{\n\t\tName:      caCertConfig.Name,\n\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n\t}\n\n\tsourceConfigMap := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, sourceConfigMapKey, sourceConfigMap); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"failed to fetch CA certificate ConfigMap %s/%s\", sourceConfigMapKey.Namespace, sourceConfigMapKey.Name)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.updateWatchLabel(sourceConfigMap, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to update watch label on CA certificate ConfigMap %s/%s\", sourceConfigMapKey.Namespace, sourceConfigMapKey.Name)\n\t}\n\n\tif _, exists := sourceConfigMap.Data[caCertConfig.Key]; !exists {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.NewIrrecoverableError(fmt.Errorf(\"key %q not found in ConfigMap %s/%s\", caCertConfig.Key, sourceConfigMapKey.Namespace, sourceConfigMapKey.Name), \"invalid CA certificate ConfigMap %s/%s\", sourceConfigMapKey.Namespace, sourceConfigMapKey.Name)\n\t}\n\n\tpemData := sourceConfigMap.Data[caCertConfig.Key]\n\tif err := r.validatePEMData(pemData); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"invalid PEM data in CA certificate ConfigMap %s/%s key %q\", sourceConfigMapKey.Namespace, sourceConfigMapKey.Name, caCertConfig.Key)\n\t}\n\n\thash, err := r.createOrUpdateCAConfigMap(istiocsr, pemData, resourceLabels)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err, \"failed to create CA certificate ConfigMap copy\")\n\t}\n\n\tupdateVolumeWithIssuerCA(deployment)\n\n\treturn hash, nil\n}\n```\n\n**f)** `updateVolumes` returns `(string, error)`:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) updateVolumes(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (string, error) {\n\tif istiocsr.Spec.IstioCSRConfig.CertManager.IstioCACertificate != nil {\n\t\thash, err := r.handleUserProvidedCA(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", common.FromError(err, \"failed to validate and mount CA certificate ConfigMap\")\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn hash, nil\n\t}\n\n\thash, err := r.handleIssuerBasedCA(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\n\treturn hash, nil\n}\n```\n\n**g)** `getDeploymentObject` uses the hash:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n\tif err := r.assertIssuerRefExists(istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to verify issuer in %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tdeployment := decodeDeploymentObjBytes(assets.MustAsset(deploymentAssetName))\n\n\tcommon.UpdateNamespace(deployment, istiocsr.GetNamespace())\n\tcommon.UpdateResourceLabels(deployment, resourceLabels)\n\tupdatePodTemplateLabels(deployment, resourceLabels)\n\n\tupdateArgList(deployment, istiocsr)\n\n\tif err := updateResourceRequirement(deployment, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update resource requirements: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := updateAffinityRules(deployment, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update affinity rules: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := updatePodTolerations(deployment, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update pod tolerations: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := updateNodeSelector(deployment, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update node selector: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tif err := r.updateImage(deployment); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"failed to update image %s/%s\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName())\n\t}\n\tcaBundleHash, err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update volume %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\tif caBundleHash != \"\" {\n\t\tupdateCABundleHashAnnotation(deployment, caBundleHash)\n\t}\n\n\treturn deployment, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 4: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go` — Add template annotation comparison\n\nIn the `deploymentSpecModified` function, add a check for pod template annotations. After the template labels check (line ~316-319), add:\n\n```diff\n \tif !reflect.DeepEqual(desired.Spec.Template.Labels, fetched.Spec.Template.Labels) ||\n+\t\t!maps.Equal(desired.Spec.Template.Annotations, fetched.Spec.Template.Annotations) ||\n \t\tlen(desired.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) != len(fetched.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) {\n \t\treturn true\n \t}\n```\n\nThe `maps` package is already imported in `utils.go`.\n\n---\n\n### File 5: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go` (NEW)\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\tappsv1 \"k8s.io/api/apps/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\nfunc TestComputeCABundleHash(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname      string\n\t\tbundle1   string\n\t\tbundle2   string\n\t\twantEqual bool\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"same content produces same hash\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBxxx\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBxxx\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"different content produces different hash\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nAAAA\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nBBBB\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"empty vs non-empty produces different hash\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"data\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: false,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\thash1 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle1)\n\t\t\thash2 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle2)\n\t\t\tif (hash1 == hash2) != tt.wantEqual {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"computeCABundleHash equality = %v, want %v (h1=%s, h2=%s)\",\n\t\t\t\t\thash1 == hash2, tt.wantEqual, hash1, hash2)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestComputeCABundleHash_Deterministic(t *testing.T) {\n\tbundle := \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\"\n\th1 := computeCABundleHash(bundle)\n\th2 := computeCABundleHash(bundle)\n\tif h1 != h2 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"hash not deterministic: %s != %s\", h1, h2)\n\t}\n\tif len(h1) != 64 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected 64-char hex SHA-256 hash, got length %d\", len(h1))\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdateCABundleHashAnnotation(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname                string\n\t\texistingAnnotations map[string]string\n\t\thash                string\n\t\twantAnnotations     map[string]string\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:                \"nil annotations\",\n\t\t\texistingAnnotations: nil,\n\t\t\thash:                \"abc123\",\n\t\t\twantAnnotations:     map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"abc123\"},\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:                \"empty annotations\",\n\t\t\texistingAnnotations: map[string]string{},\n\t\t\thash:                \"def456\",\n\t\t\twantAnnotations:     map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"def456\"},\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:                \"preserves existing annotations\",\n\t\t\texistingAnnotations: map[string]string{\"other\": \"value\"},\n\t\t\thash:                \"ghi789\",\n\t\t\twantAnnotations:     map[string]string{\"other\": \"value\", caBundleHashAnnotation: \"ghi789\"},\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:                \"overwrites stale hash\",\n\t\t\texistingAnnotations: map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"old-hash\"},\n\t\t\thash:                \"new-hash\",\n\t\t\twantAnnotations:     map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"new-hash\"},\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tdep := &appsv1.Deployment{\n\t\t\t\tSpec: appsv1.DeploymentSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplate: corev1.PodTemplateSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAnnotations: tt.existingAnnotations,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tupdateCABundleHashAnnotation(dep, tt.hash)\n\t\t\tgot := dep.Spec.Template.Annotations\n\t\t\tif len(got) != len(tt.wantAnnotations) {\n\t\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"annotation count = %d, want %d\", len(got), len(tt.wantAnnotations))\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tfor k, v := range tt.wantAnnotations {\n\t\t\t\tif got[k] != v {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"annotation[%q] = %q, want %q\", k, got[k], v)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestDeploymentSpecModified_TemplateAnnotations(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname     string\n\t\tdesired  *appsv1.Deployment\n\t\tfetched  *appsv1.Deployment\n\t\twantTrue bool\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"both nil annotations\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\treturn baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\treturn baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"desired has hash annotation, fetched has none\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"abc123\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched:  baseDeployment(1, \"img\"),\n\t\t\twantTrue: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"hash annotation changed\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"new-hash\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"old-hash\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"same hash annotation\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"same-hash\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"same-hash\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: false,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tgot := deploymentSpecModified(tt.desired, tt.fetched)\n\t\t\tif got != tt.wantTrue {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"deploymentSpecModified() = %v, want %v\", got, tt.wantTrue)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# From the repository root:\n\n# 1. Run unit tests to verify the changes compile and pass\nmake test\n\n# Or just the unit tests for the istiocsr package:\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n\n# 2. Run vet\nmake vet\n\n# 3. Full verify\nmake verify\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of the idempotency guard\n\nThe idempotency works at two levels:\n\n1. **ConfigMap level**: `createOrUpdateCAConfigMap` checks `hasObjectChanged(desired, fetched)` — if the ConfigMap data hasn't changed, it skips the update. Since the hash is computed from the same `certData`, an unchanged ConfigMap means an unchanged hash.\n\n2. **Deployment level**: `createOrApplyDeployments` checks `hasObjectChanged(desired, fetched)` which calls `deploymentSpecModified`. The updated `deploymentSpecModified` now compares `Spec.Template.Annotations` (including the hash annotation). When the hash is the same, `deploymentSpecModified` returns false, and the `UpdateWithRetry` call is skipped entirely. Only when the CA PEM content changes does the hash change, causing the annotation to differ, triggering the deployment update and thus a rolling restart."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":192,"cache_read_input_tokens":117393,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":192,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70c02473-b6cc-430a-bbaf-9126673321a3","uuid":"867c3842-9061-4056-84a2-6de0c944b21d","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18:26:42.671Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDn7ooDXxd2CdykLtmb3"}
